comment: Idempotence of the interior function is equivalent to stating a set, ` s ` , is a neighborhood of a point, ` x ` is equivalent to there existing a special neighborhood, ` u ` , of ` x ` such that a point is an element of the special neighborhood if and only if ` s ` is also a neighborhood of the point.
